UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.On Player Enters: A player enters the spawned vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.On Player Exits: A player exits the spawned vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.On Vehicle Spawn: A vehicle is spawned or respawned.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Apply OffRoad Ti: Apply off-road tires to the vehicle if the vehicle can receive them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.FuelUseMultiplie: Controls how quickly the vehicle will use fuel while driving.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Vehicle Health.D: Determines how much damage the vehicle can take before destruction.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Vehicle Indestru: Determines if the Vehicle can be destroyed by damage.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Destroy when Stu: Determines if the Vehicle will destroy itself when stuck underwater.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.EnableRespawn.De: Determines if the Vehicle will respawn after being destroyed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Fuel Consumption: Determines if the spawned vehicle uses fuel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Enabled During P: Determines the game phases during which the device will be enabled. If set to CREATE ONLY, will only be enabled while editing your Island.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Max Random Start: Determines the maximum random fuel percentage the vehicle will spawn with. If Max is less than or equal to Min, the vehicle will spawn with default fuel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Min Random Start: Determines the minimum random fuel percentage the vehicle will spawn with. If Max is less than or equal to Min, the vehicle will spawn with default fuel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Visible During G: Determines whether the device is visible during the game. This does affect its collision properties.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Disable.Descript: Disable the Vehicle Spawner, stopping it from spawning any more vehicles.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Enable.Descripti: Enable the Vehicle Spawner, allowing it to spawn vehicles.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Allowed Class.De: If set to All, All Classes (including players with NO CLASS) are affected. Otherwise, the chosen Class will be used to determine the Affects Class effect. ANY CLASS - Players with a Class assigned, regardless of what Class it is. NO CLASS - Players without any assigned class.

UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Destroy Vehicle: ON will destroy an already spawned vehicle when this spawner is disabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Pop All Tires.De: Pop all of the tires on the vehicle, if the vehicle has tires to pop.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Repair All Tires: Repair all of the tires on the vehicle, if the vehicle has tires to repair.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Repair Vehicle.D: Restore the spawned vehicle to full health.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Remove Tire Modi: Revert to road tires on the vehicle if the vehicle can receive them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Assigns Driver.D: Seats the player that instigated the message as the spawned vehicle's driver.

UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Starting Fuel.De: The percentage of fuel in the vehicle's fuel tank at spawn.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Water Destructio: When the vehicle becomes too deep in water to drive, destroy it after this delay.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Respawn Time.Des: When the vehicle is destroyed, respawn it after this delay. (The first vehicle spawned does not use this delay.)
UserOptionDefinition.Device_TankSpawner_V2_C.Respawn Vehicle: YES will spawn a vehicle when the device is enabled. ONLY IF NEEDED will not reset an existing vehicle.
